cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.LO, cs.SY

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it investigates the use of lexicase parent selection in Learning Classifier Systems (LCS) and studies its effect on classification problems in a supervised setting. It also introduces a new variant of lexicase selection, called batch-lexicase selection, which allows for the tuning of selection pressure. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with evolutionary machine learning methods. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) as LCS is a rule-based machine learning method that uses logical expressions to represent knowledge. 

Finally, it could be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as LCS has been applied in control systems and robotics.
